headline: RCL Q1 Earnings Call: Management Focuses on Demand Resilience and Expanding Fleet for 2025
summary: Cruise vacation company Royal Caribbean (NYSE:RCL) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025, with sales up 7.3% year on year to $4 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.71 per share was 7% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
